        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 6:43PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 643 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Xenia to near Irvington to near Sparta.
Movement was southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Vernon, Pinckneyville, Rend Lake Area, Wayne City, Woodlawn,
Bluford, Cisne, Tamaroa, Dix, Cutler, Waltonville, Bonnie, Nason,
Keenes, and Johnsonville.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 57 in Illinois between Mile Markers 86 and 105.
Interstate 64 in Illinois between Mile Markers 63 and 88.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
